	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />It depends on the type of game, but I do feel a basic understanding of math and physics helps. While working on a Zelda-type game, everything was very simple and basic. On the other hand, a platformer project was a lot more complex. Some of that was by choice, such as having elastic collisions instead of simple ejections. It's really a matter of how far you want to take the simulation vs approximating things.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
